Content:: Seeniththamby Yogeswaran (Tamil: சீனித்தம்பி யோகேஸ்வரன்; born 26 April 1970) is a Sri Lankan Tamil politician and Member of Parliament. Yogeswaran was born on 26 April 1970.[1] Yogeswaran was one of the Tamil National Alliance's candidates for Batticaloa District at the 2010 parliamentary election. He was elected and entered Parliament.[2] He was re-elected at the 2015 parliamentary election.[3][4][5]
